        "app_readme": "<h1>Readarr</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Readarr/Readarr\">Readarr</a> is an ebook and audiobook collection manager for Usenet and BitTorrent users.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>When application is installed, a container will be launched with <strong>root</strong> privileges.\nThis is required in order to apply the correct permissions to the <code>Readarr</code> directories.\nAfterward, the <code>Readarr</code> container will run as a <strong>non</strong>-root user (Default: <code>568</code>).\nAll mounted storage(s) will be <code>chown</code>ed only if the parent directory does not match the configured user.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "detailed_readme": "<h1>Readarr</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Readarr/Readarr\">Readarr</a> is an ebook and audiobook collection manager for Usenet and BitTorrent users.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>When application is installed, a container will be launched with <strong>root</strong> privileges.\nThis is required in order to apply the correct permissions to the <code>Readarr</code> directories.\nAfterward, the <code>Readarr</code> container will run as a <strong>non</strong>-root user (Default: <code>568</code>).\nAll mounted storage(s) will be <code>chown</code>ed only if the parent directory does not match the configured user.</p>\n</blockquote>",
